SIMPLE: healthful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Healthful
<hw>Health"ful</hw> <pr>(-f⟦usdot⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Full of health; free from illness or disease; well; whole; sound;
healthy; <as>as, a <ex>healthful</ex> body or mind; a <ex>healthful</ex>
plant.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Serving to promote health of body or mind;
wholesome; salubrious; salutary; <as>as, a <ex>healthful</ex> air,
diet</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>healthful</qex> Spirit of thy grace.</q> <rj><qau>Book of
Common Prayer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Indicating, characterized by, or resulting from,
health or soundness; <as>as, a <ex>healthful</ex>
condition</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A mind . . . <qex>healthful</qex> and so well-proportioned.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Well-disposed; favorable.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gave <qex>healthful</qex> welcome to their shipwrecked guests.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Healthfully</ent>⟦br⟧
